Text: Playing our roles.
Speaker: Petyr Baelish

Text: (Joffrey arrives, Varys bows)  Serving a new King.
Speaker: Varys

Text: Long may he reign. My king. (bows)
Speaker: Petyr Baelish

Text: My king.
Speaker: Varys

Text: My lords. Shall we begin?
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: You're Arry now, hear me? Arry the orphan boy. No one asks an orphan too many questions, ‘cause nobody gives three shits. What's your name?
Speaker: Yoren

Text: Arry.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: You've a long way to travel, and in bad company. l've 20 this time –  men and boys all bound for the Wall. Your lord father gave me the pick of the dungeons, and l didn't find no little lordlings down there. This lot – half of them would turn you over to the King quick as spit for a pardon. And the other half would do the same, except they'd rape you first. So keep to yourself – and when you piss, do it in the woods alone. You stay with this lot, boy. And stay or l'll lock you in the back of the wagon with these three.
Speaker: Yoren

Text: Watch yourself, midget.
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: What's a gutter rat like you doing with a sword?
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: He ain't no squire. Look at him. He looks like a girl. l bet he stole that sword.
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: l could use me a sword like that.
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: Give it here, midget.
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: l knocked him down and l kicked him in the balls and l kept kicking him until he was dead. l kicked him all to pieces. You better give me that sword!
Speaker: Hot Pie

Text: (pointing Needle at Hot Pie) You want it? l'll give it to you. l already killed one fat boy. l bet you never killed anyone. l bet you're a liar. But l'm not. l'm good at killing fat boys. l like killing fat boys.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Your like picking on the little ones, do you? l've been hammering an anvil these past 10 years. When l hit that steel, it sings. Are you gonna sing when l hit you? (Hot Pie leaves, scared. Gendry talks to Arya alone) This is castle-forged steel. Where'd you steal it?
Speaker: Gendry

Text: lt was a gift.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: lt don't matter now. Where we're going, they don't care what you've done. They've got rapers, pickpockets, highwaymen, murderers.
Speaker: Gendry

Text: Which are you?
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Armourer's apprentice. But my master got sick of me, so here l am.
Speaker: Gendry

Text: (shouting) Come on, you sorry sons of whores! lt's a thousand leagues from here to the Wall, and winter is coming!
Speaker: Yoren

Text: Ham. How many days in a row must a man be expected to start his day with ham? Bring me some beer at least. You look exhausted. Was your moonlight ride that tiring?
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: My friends brought me back.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: l didn't say it was your honor.
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: They killed my father.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: And you're gonna bring him back to life, are you? No? Good. We've had enough of that sort of thing. Beyond the Wall, the Rangers are reporting whole villages abandoned. At night they see fires blazing in the mountains from dusk until dawn. A captured wildling swears their tribes are uniting in some secret stronghold, to what ends the gods only know. Outside Eastwatch Cotter Pyke's men discovered four blue-eyed corpses. Unlike us, they were wise enough to burn them. Do you think your brother's war is more important than ours?
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: No.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: When dead men and worse come hunting for us in the night, do you think it matters who sits on the lron Throne?
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: No.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Good. Because l want you and your wolf with us when we ride out beyond the Wall tomorrow.
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: Beyond the Wall?
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: l'll not sit meekly by and wait for the snows. l mean to find out what's happening. The Night's Watch will ride in force against the wildlings, the White Walkers and whatever else is out there. And we will find Benjen Stark, alive or dead. l will command them myself. So l'll only ask you once, Lord Snow, are you a brother of the Night's Watch or a bastard boy who wants to play at war?
Speaker: Jeor Mormont

Text: (picking up the dragon eggs from their chest, speaking in Dothraki) ls this your command, Khaleesi? (Daenerys nods, Rakharo places the eggs next to Drogo’s funeral pyre)
Speaker: Rakharo

Text: Drogo will have no use for dragon eggs in the Night Lands. Sell them. You can return to the Free Cities and live as a wealthy woman for all your days.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: They were not given to me to sell.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Khaleesi, my Queen, l vow to serve you, obey you, to die for you if need be, but let him go, Khaleesi. l know what you intend. Do not.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: l must. You don't understand.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Don't ask me to stand aside as you climb on that pyre. l won't watch you burn.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: ls that what you fear? (kisses Jorah on the cheek, then speaks to the rest of the Dothraki and Lhazareen who stayed with her)  You will be my khalasar. l see the faces of slaves. l free you. Take off your collars. Go if you wish, no one will stop you. But if you stay it will be as brothers and sisters, as husbands and wives.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Ser Jorah, bind this woman to the pyre. You swore to obey me.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: You will not hear me scream.
Speaker: Mirri Maz Duur

Text: I will. But it is not your screams I want. Only your life.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: (bowing)  Blood of my blood.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: You need to drink, child... And eat.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: Isn't there anything else?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: The Dothraki have two things in abundance: grass and horses. People can't live on grass... In the Shadow Lands beyond Asshai, they say there are fields of ghost grass with stalks as pale as milk that glow in the night. It murders all other grass. The Dothraki believe that one day it will cover everything. That's the way the world will end… It'll get easier.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: Khaleesi!
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Your hands.
Speaker: Irri

Text: We're still not far from Pentos, your Grace. Magister Illyrio has extended his hospitality. You'd be more comfortable there.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: I have no interest in hospitality or comfort. I'll stay with Drogo until he fulfils his end of the bargain and I have my crown.
Speaker: Viserys Targaryen

Text: As you wish, your Grace.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: Well, Mormont, as brutish as this life is, I suppose it is preferable to beheading. What did Ned Stark want you for? Buying from a slaver?
Speaker: Viserys Targaryen

Text: Selling to one... Some poachers I caught on my land.
Speaker: Jorah Mormont

Text: Under my reign, you won't be punished for such nonsense. You can rest assured of that.
Speaker: Viserys Targaryen

Text: Better-looking bitches than you're used to, Uncle. My mother's been looking for you. We ride for King's Landing today.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Before you go, you will call on Lord and Lady Stark and offer your sympathies.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: What good will my sympathies do them?
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: None. But it is expected of you. Your absence has already been noted.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: The boy means nothing to me. And I can't stand the wailing of women.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: One word and I'll hit you again.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: I'm telling mother!
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Go! Tell her. But first you will get to Lord and Lady Stark and you will fall on your knees in front of them and tell them how very sorry you are, that you are at their service, and that all your prayers are with them. Do you understand?
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: You can't...
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Do you understand?
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: The Prince will remember that, little lord.
Speaker: Sandor Clegane

Text: I hope so. If he forgets, be a good dog and remind him. Time for breakfast...
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Bread. And two of those little fish. And a mug of dark beer to wash it down. And bacon, burnt black.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Little brother.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: Beloved siblings.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Is Bran going to die?
Speaker: Myrcella Baratheon

Text: Apparently not.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: The Maester says the boy may live.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Only the gods know for certain. All the rest of us can do is pray. The charms of the north seem entirely lost on you.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Where's your sense of wonder? The greatest structure ever built, the intrepid men of the Night's Watch, the wintry abode of the White Walkers.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Tell me you're not thinking of taking the black.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: And go celibate? The whores would go begging from Dorne to Casterly Rock. I just want to stand on top of the Wall and piss off the edge of the world.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Even if the boy lives, he'll be a cripple, a grotesque. Give me a good clean death any day.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: Speaking for the grotesques, I'd have to disagree. Death is so final, whereas life... Life is full of possibilities. I hope the boy does wake. I'd be very interested to hear what he has to say.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: My dear brother, there are times you make me wonder whose side you're on.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: My dear brother, you wound me. You know how much I love my family.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: I would have dressed, your Grace.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I never knew.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I am grateful..
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: A sword for the wall?
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: I already have one.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Good man. Have you swung it yet?
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: Of course I have.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: At someone, I mean. It's a strange thing, the first time you cut a man. You realize we're nothing but sacks of meat and blood and some bone to keep it all standing. Let me thank you ahead of time for guarding us all from the perils beyond the Wall... Wildlings and White Walkers and whatnot. We're grateful to have good, strong men like you protecting us.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: We've guarded the Kingdoms for 8 000 years.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Is it "we" already? Have you taken your vows then?
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: Soon enough.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Give my regards to the Night's Watch. I'm sure it will be thrilling to serve in such an elite force. And if not, It's only for life.
Speaker: Jaime Lannister

Text: Thank you, Nymeria. Septa Mordane says I have to do it again. "My things weren't properly folded", she says. Who cares how they're folded?! They're going to get all messed up anyway.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: It's good you've got help.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Watch. Nymeria, gloves.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Impressive.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Shut up. Nymeria, gloves!
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: I have something for you. And it has to be packed very carefully.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: A present?
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Close the door. This is no toy. Be careful you don't cut yourself.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: It's so skinny.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: So are you. I had the blacksmith make it for you special. It won't hack a man's head off, but it can poke him full of holes if you're quick enough.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: I can be quick.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: You'll have to work at it every day. How does it feel? Do you like the balance?
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: I think so.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: First lesson: Stick them with the pointy end.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: I know which end to use.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: I'm going to miss you... Careful... All the best swords have names, you know.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Sansa can keep her sewing needles. I've got a needle of my own.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: I came to say goodbye to Bran.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: You've said it.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I wish I could be here when you wake up. I'm going north with Uncle Benjen. I'm taking the black. I know we always talked about seeing the Wall together, but you'll be able to come visit me at Castle Black when you're better. I'll know my way around by then. I'll be a sworn brother of the Night's Watch. We can go out walking beyond the Wall, if you're not afraid.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: I want you to leave.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: 17 years ago you rode off with Robert Baratheon. You came back a year later with another woman's son. And now you're leaving again.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I have no choice.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: That's what men always say when honor calls. That's what you tell your families, tell yourselves. You do have a choice. And you've made it. I can't do it, Ned. I really can't.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: You can. You must.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: You've said goodbye to Bran? He's not going to die. I know it.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: You Starks are hard to kill.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: My mother?
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: She was very kind.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Good. Next time I see you, you'll be all in black.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: It was always my color.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Farewell, Snow.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: And you, Stark.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: There's great honor serving in the Night's Watch. The Starks have manned the Wall for thousands of years. And you are a Stark. You might not have my name, but you have my blood.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Is my mother alive? Does she know about me? Where I am, where I'm going? Does she care?
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: The next time we see each other, we'll talk about your mother. I promise.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Gods, this is country! I've half a mind to leave them all behind and keep going.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: I've half a mind to go with you.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: What do you say, just you and me on the Kingsroad, swords at our sides, a couple of tavern wenches to warm our beds tonight.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: You should have asked me 20 years ago.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: There were wars to fight, women to marry... We never had the chance to be young.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: I recall a few chances.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: There was that one... Oh, what was her name? That common girl of yours? Becca? With the great big tits you could bury your face in.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Bessie. She was one of yours.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Bessie! Thank the gods for Bessie and her tits. Yours was... Aleena? No. You told me once. Meryl? Your bastard's mother?
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Wylla.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: That's it. She must have been a rare wench to make Lord Eddard Stark forget his honor. You never told me what she looked like.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Nor will I.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: We were at war. None of us knew if we were gonna go back home again. You're too hard on yourself. You always have been. I swear if I weren't your King, you'd have hit me already.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: The worst thing about your coronation... I'll never get to hit you again.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Trust me, that's not the worst thing. There was a rider in the night.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Daenerys Targaryen has wed some Dothraki horselord. What of it? Should we send her a wedding gift?
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: A knife perhaps, a good sharp one, and a bold man to wield it.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: She's little more than a child.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Soon enough that child will spread her legs and start breeding.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Tell me we're not speaking of this.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: Oh, it's unspeakable to you? What her father did to your family... That was unspeakable. What Rhaegar Targaryen did to your sister... the woman I loved. I'll kill every Targaryen I get my hands on.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: But you can't get your hands on this one, can you?
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: This Khal Drogo, it's said he has 100,000 men in his horde.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Even a million Dothraki are no threat to the realm, as long as they remain on the other side of the Narrow Sea. They have no ships, Robert.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: There are still those in the Seven Kingdoms who call me Usurper. If the Targaryen boy crosses with a Dothraki horde at his back, the scum will join him.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: He will not cross. And if by chance he does, we'll throw him back into the sea.
Speaker: Eddard Stark

Text: There's a war coming, Ned. I don't know when, I don't know who we'll be fighting, but it's coming.
Speaker: Robert Baratheon

Text: Sit. You'll be fed. Untie them.
Speaker: Benjen Stark

Text: Rapers. They were given a choice no doubt... Castration or the Wall. Most choose the knife. Not impressed by your new brothers? Lovely thing about the Watch... You discard your old family and get a whole new one.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Why do you read so much?
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Look at me and tell me what you see.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Is this a trick?
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: What you see is a dwarf. If I'd been born a peasant they might've left me out in the woods to die. Alas, I was born a Lannister of Casterly Rock. Things are expected of me. My father was the Hand of the King for 20 years.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Until your brother killed that King.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Yes, until my brother killed him. Life is full of these little ironies. My sister married the new King and my repulsive nephew will be King after him. I must do my part for the honor of my house, wouldn't you agree? But how? Well, my brother has his sword and I have my mind. And a mind needs books like a sword needs a whetstone. That's why I read so much. And you? What's your story, bastard?
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Ask me nicely and maybe I'll tell you, dwarf.
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: A bastard boy with nothing to inherit, off to join the ancient order of the Night's Watch, alongside his valiant brothers-in-arms.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: The Night's Watch protects the realm from...
Speaker: Jon Snow

Text: Yes yes, against grumpkins and snarks and all the other monsters your wet nurse warned you about. You're a smart boy. You don't believe that nonsense... Everything's better with some wine in the belly.
Speaker: Tyrion Lannister

Text: Talk to Poole about it.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I don't care about appointments!
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I'll make the appointments. We'll talk about it first thing in the morning.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: When was the last time you left this room?
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: I have to take care of him.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: He's not going to die, mother. Maester Luwin says the most dangerous time has passed.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: What if he's wrong? Bran needs me.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Rickon needs you. He's six. He doesn't know what's happening. He follows me around all day, clutching my leg, crying...
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: Close the windows! I can't stand it! Please make them stop! (Wolf’s howling repeatedly)
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Fire. You stay here. I'll come back.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: No!
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Have you ever seen a dragon?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Dragon gone, Khaleesi.
Speaker: Irri

Text: Everywhere? Even in the east?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: No dragon. Brave men kill them. It is known.
Speaker: Irri

Text: It is known.
Speaker: Jhiqui

Text: A trader from Garth told me that dragons come from the moon.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: The moon?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: He told me the moon was an egg, Khaleesi, that once there were two moons in the sky. But one wandered too close to the sun and it cracked from the heat. Out of it poured a thousand thousand dragons and they drank the sun's fire.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Moon is no egg. Moon is goddess... wife of sun. It is known.
Speaker: Irri

Text: It is known.
Speaker: Jhiqui

Text: Leave me with her. Why did the trader from Garth tell you these stories?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Men like to talk when they're happy. Before your brother bought me for you, it was my job to make men happy.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: How old were you?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: I was nine when my mother sold me to the pleasure house.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Nine?!
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: I did not touch a man for three years, Khaleesi. First you must learn.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Can you teach me how to make the Khal happy?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Yes.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Will it take three years?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: No.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Welcome.
Speaker: Benjen Stark

Text: What I am about to tell you must remain between us. I don't think Bran fell from that tower. I think he was thrown.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Someone tried to kill him twice. Why? Why murder an innocent child? Unless he saw something he wasn't meant to see.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Saw what, my lady?
Speaker: Theon Greyjoy

Text: I don't know. But I would stake my life the Lannisters are involved. We already have reason to suspect their loyalty to the crown.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: They come into our home and try to murder my brother? If it's war they want...
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: If it comes to that, you know I'll stand behind you.
Speaker: Theon Greyjoy

Text: I don't trust a raven to carry these words.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: I'll ride to King's Landing.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: No. There must always be a Stark in Winterfell. I will go myself.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Mother, you can't.
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: I must.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: Too large a party attracts unwanted attention. I don't want the Lannisters to know I'm coming.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: What about Bran?
Speaker: Robb Stark

Text: I have prayed to the Seven for more than a month. Bran's life is in their hands now.
Speaker: Catelyn Stark

Text: No, Khaleesi. You must look in his eyes always. Love comes in at the eyes. It is said that Irogenia of Lys could finish a man with nothing but her eyes.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Finish a man?
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Kings traveled across the world for a night with Irogenia. Magisters sold their palaces. Khals burned her enemies just to have her for a few hours. They say a thousand men proposed to her and she refused them all.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: Well, she sounds like an interesting woman. I don't think that Drogo will like it with me on top.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: You will make him like it, Khaleesi. Men want what they've never had. And the Dothraki take slaves like a hound takes a bitch. Are you a slave, Khaleesi? Then don't make love like a slave. Very good, Khaleesi. Out there he is the mighty Khal, but in this tent, he belongs to you.
Speaker: Doreah

Text: I don't think that this is the Dothraki way.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: If he wanted the Dothraki way, why did he marry you?
Speaker: Doreah

Text: No. No. Tonight I would look upon your face.
Speaker: Daenerys Targaryen

Text: Pardon me, Ser.
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: Do I frighten you so much, girl? Or is it him there making you shake? He frightens me too. Look at that face.
Speaker: Sandor Clegane

Text: I'm sorry if I offended you, Ser. Why won't he speak to me?
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: He hasn't been very talkative these last 20 years. Since the mad King had his tongue ripped out with hot pincers.
Speaker: Sandor Clegane

Text: He speaks damn well with his sword though. Ser Ilyn Payne, the King's justice. The royal executioner. What is it, sweet lady? Does the hound frighten you? Away with you, dog. You're scaring my lady. I don't like to see you upset. The sun is finally shining. Come walk with me.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Stay, Lady. I probably shouldn't have any more. Father only lets us have one cup at feasts.
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: My princess can drink as much as she wants. Don't worry... You're safe with me.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: I'll get you!
Speaker: Mycah

Text: Arya!
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: What are you doing here? Go away.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Your sister? And who are you, boy?
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Mycah, my Lord.
Speaker: Mycah

Text: He the butcher's boy.
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: He's my friend.
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: A butcher's boy who wants to be a Knight, eh? Pick up your sword, butcher's boy. Let's see how good you are.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: She asked me to, my Lord. She asked me to.
Speaker: Mycah

Text: I'm your prince, not your lord, and I said pick up your sword.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: It's not a sword, my prince. It's only a stick.
Speaker: Mycah

Text: And you're not a Knight. Only a butcher's boy. That was my lady's sister you were hitting, do you know that?
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Stop it!
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Arya, stay out of this.
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: I won't hurt him... Much. Filthy little bitch!
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: No no, stop it, stop it, both of you. You're spoiling it. You're spoiling everything!
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: I'll gut you, you little cunt!
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: Arya!
Speaker: Sansa Stark

Text: Nymeria!
Speaker: Arya Stark

Text: Please don't.
Speaker: Joffrey Baratheon

Text: When I was 12, my mother and father went to a wedding. Weddings in Volantis last for days, you know. And they left me with my little brother. The second afternoon they were gone was the hottest day in the three-year summer. We couldn't bear to be inside, so we ran down to the Rhoyne. Every child in Volantis was in the Rhoyne that day. The rich, the poor, we were all there. Naked, screaming, racing to the little islands. Drummers were playing for coppers on the east bank. I was treading water, talking to a friend, when I realized I hadn't seen my brother. I called his name. Then I started screaming his name. And then I saw him floating face down. My heart just stopped. I was I dragged him from the water. My friend helped me, I think. I don't even remember. He was so little. Then we pulled him onto the riverbank. And I screamed at him and I shook him. And he was dead. Just dead. A man ran over. He had a fish tattoo on his face. In Volantis, the slaves have tattoos. So you know what they are without having to talk to them. And this man worked on a fishing boat. And he pushed me out of the way. You have to understand, for a slave to push a highborn girl, that's death for the man, a terrible death. But he pushed me out of the way, and he started pressing on my brother's chest again and again and again, until my brother spat out half of the Rhoyne and cried out. And the man cradled his head and told him to be calm. I decided two things that day. I would not waste my years planning dances and masquerades with the other noble ladies.
